Name: PAutomata
Title:Parameterized automata
Author:Emmanuel Freund & Christine Paulin 
Institution: LRI, Université Paris Sud

Description: This contribution is a modelisation in Coq of the p-automata 
designed in the CALIFE project (http://www.loria.fr/calife). 
It contains an axiomatisation of time, 
the definition of a p-automaton, the definition of binary and 
arbitrary synchronisation of a family of p-automaton, the semantics of 
a p-automaton as a labelled transition system. The description of the ABR 
algorithm as a p-automaton is also given.

This work is reported in : P. Castéran, E. Freund, C. Paulin and
D. Rouillard ``Bibliothèques Coq et Isabelle-HOL pour les systèmes de
transitions et les p-automates''
http://www.loria.fr/projets/calife/WebCalifePublic/FOURNITURES/F5.4.ps.gz
Fourniture CALIFE 2000


The files Evenements.v and ABRgen.v contain a proof of a general 
ABR algorithm with an unlimited schedule proposed by C. Rabadan & F. Klay. 
This modelisation does not use p-automaton

The directory PGM contains a modelisation of the Pragmatic General
Multicast (PGM) multicast internet protocol as a p-automata done by Yijia Chen.
in august 2001 at LRI, Université Paris Sud with Coq Version: 7.1

Keywords: p-automata, ABR, PGM, time
Version: 7.0
